      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): skip runtime cron promotion",
        "body": "## Summary\n- skip the internal runtime-only event prompt and its immediate assistant response when exporting session JSONL for memory ingestion\n- persist an internal `__openclaw.runtimeOnlyEvent` marker on runtime-only user prompts so user-typed marker text cannot suppress real assistant replies\n- extend memory-core/session-reader coverage so cron delivery report text does not become short-term promotion evidence\n- add a changelog entry for #79507\n\nFixes #79507.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** #79507 reported that runtime-generated cron delivery report text could be treated as short-term memory promotion evidence during dreaming/session-corpus ingestion. The review also flagged a spoofing risk where a real user typing `Continue the OpenClaw runtime event.` could hide the next assistant reply.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw checkout on Windows 11, Node v22.15.0, branch `hemant/fix-memory-cron-promotion` at `f686706223` after rebasing onto `upstream/main` `4089c557c0`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran `node --import tsx --input-type=module -e ...` from the repo root. The script created two real JSONL transcript files and called the real memory host `buildSessionEntry` reader: one transcript with `__openclaw.runtimeOnlyEvent: true` on the generated marker prompt, and one transcript where a user typed the same visible marker without internal provenance.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Copied terminal output from that local run:\n```json\n{\n  \"flaggedContent\": \"User: Remember the database maintenance window.\\nAssistant: I noted the database maintenance window.\",\n  \"flaggedContainsRuntimeReport\": false,\n  \"spoofContent\": \"User: Continue the OpenClaw runtime event.\\nAssistant: That text is now part of the conversation.\",\n  \"spoofKeepsAssistantReply\": true\n}\n```\n- **Observed result after fix:** Runtime-marked event turns and their generated delivery report are excluded from session-corpus export, while the same visible text from a real user remains in the export together with the assistant reply.\n- **What was not tested:** Full `extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-phases.test.ts` on this Windows host still has unrelated existing local failures around fs-safe append guards and one multi-sweep expectation; the touched behavior was covered by the focused memory-core corpus case and host/session guard tests listed below.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 CHANGELOG.md extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-phases.test.ts src/sessions/runtime-only-event-provenance.ts src/agents/session-tool-result-guard-wrapper.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.ts src/agents/session-tool-result-guard.tool-result-persist-hook.test.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/openclaw-runtime.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/openclaw-runtime-session.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/session-files.ts packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/session-files.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main..HEAD`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 pnpm test packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/session-files.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 pnpm test src/agents/session-tool-result-guard.tool-result-persist-hook.test.ts -t \"marks only the requested persisted user message\" -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-phases.test.ts -t \"drops archive, cron, and heartbeat chatter\" -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `node --import tsx --input-type=module -e ...` real transcript proof above\n- `pnpm check:changed --base upstream/main`\n\nNote: this host has Node v22.15.0, so pnpm emitted the repo engine warning (`>=22.16.0` required) before the commands above; the commands still completed successfully.",
